data.name: treestartr
data.description: An R package for making starting trees from combined molecular, morphological and stratigraphic data

evidence: "treeStartR is an R package for auomated generation of starting trees for total-evidence phylogenetic analyses."

Usage shows it being loaded as a library: "library(treestartr)" and then its functions (e.g., `present_tippr`, `rand_absent_tippr`) are called from R code, indicating it is a reusable package dependency.

Installation is described via GitHub source: "Install the development version directly from Github" followed by `install_github("wrightaprilm/treeStartR")`, with no mention of CRAN or other registries. The package directly generates starting trees used in phylogenetic analyses, i.e., core research outputs.
